{"word":"ζωογονέω","slug":"ζωογονέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ζωογονέω</el></b> [<el>ζωός</el> ‘alive’, <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:γίνομαι\">γίνομαι</a></el> via <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:γενέσθαι\">γενέσθαι</a></el>] <b>keep/preserve alive <a href='B:490 17:33'>Lk 17:33</a>; <a href='B:510 7:19'>Ac 7:19</a>; <a href='B:610 6:13'>1 Ti 6:13</a></b> (many render ‘give life to’, but the context appears to suggest encouragement in the face of difficulties)<b>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ζώννυμι/ζωννύω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ζῷον\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}